<!--<para id="fs-id1167067217086"><link class="os-embed" url="#ost/api/ex/k12phys-ch12-ex003"/></para>-->
<para id="fs-id1164564284279">What is the zeroth law of thermodynamics?</para>
<list id="fs-id1164565858862" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
<item>Energy can neither be created nor destroyed in a chemical reaction.</item>
<item>If two systems, A and B, are in thermal equilibrium with each another, and B is in thermal equilibrium with a third system, C, then A is also in thermal equilibrium with C.</item>
<item>Entropy of any isolated system not in thermal equilibrium always increases.</item>
<item>Entropy of a system approaches a constant value as temperature approaches absolute zero.</item>
</list>
</problem>
