<section id="fs-id1167067217364" class="summary">
<title>Section Summary</title>
<list id="fs-id1167067272112">
<item>Systems are in thermal equilibrium when they have the same temperature.</item>
<item>Thermal equilibrium occurs when two bodies are in contact with each other and can freely exchange energy.</item>
<item>The zeroth law of thermodynamics states that when two systems, A and B, are in thermal equilibrium with each other, and B is in thermal equilibrium with a third system, C, then A is also in thermal equilibrium with C.</item>
</list>
</section>



<section id="fs-id1167063429291" class="concept"><title>Concept Items</title>
