<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1167067200298">
<term>thermal equilibrium</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167063647290">condition in which heat no longer transfers energy between two objects that are in contact; the two objects have the same temperature</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1167063852322">
<term>zeroth law of thermodynamics</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1167067111711">states that if two objects are in thermal equilibrium, and a third object is in thermal equilibrium with one of those objects, it is also in thermal equilibrium with the other object</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
